  "prompt": "How fast can helicopters travel?",
  "response": "The speed of helicopters can vary widely depending on their design, purpose, and model. Generally, most civilian helicopters have a cruising speed ranging from 120 to 160 mph (approximately 193 to 257 km/h). Military helicopters and some advanced civilian models can fly faster. For example, the Eurocopter X\u00b3, an experimental helicopter, reached speeds over 290 mph (approximately 467 km/h). Typically, the speed is limited by factors such as rotor design and aerodynamic efficiency.",
